Don’t toss your scraps just yet. Honor Earth Day with this delicious low-waste pasta sauce recipe that turns plant stems into the stars of the meal—featuring broccoli, herb, and cauliflower stems, carrot tops, garlic and onion skins, and lemon peel.

INGREDIENTS
3 cups of any green veggie scraps you have on hand (like broccoli, cauliflower, and herb stems, carrot tops, and/or beet greens)
4 cloves skin-on garlic, smashed
1 skin-on shallot or ¼ onion, chopped
¼ cup mushroom stems, chopped 
Lemon peel or juice from one small lemon
⅓ cup seeds (like pumpkin, sunflower, hemp, or pine nuts)
2 tablespoons olive oil
Salt + pepper to taste
2 servings of cooked pasta 

DIRECTIONS
1. Sauté garlic + onion skins in oiled pan until fragrant and softened. 
2. Add in finely chopped mushroom stems and sauté, stirring often for 2 minutes. 
3. Add sautéed garlic, onion, and mushrooms into a blender with all the greens, vegetable scraps, and lemon peel. Blend on high, adding water until the sauce is to your preferred consistency.
4. Add in seeds and olive oil and blend again until smooth. 
5. Transfer sauce to a pot and heat gently over low. Add salt and pepper to taste.
6. Drop cooked pasta into the sauce and coat well. 
7. Top with seeds and red pepper flakes and enjoy!

Save This: Basil Lime Elixir

This refreshing spring elixir gets a boost of functional hydration and its emerald hue from Sakara Detox Water Drops, for a libation that's as healthful as it is delicious. Cheers, Sakaralite! 

2 Sprigs of basil
2 Sprigs of mint
1-2 Droppers of Sakara Detox Water Drops
Juice from 1/2 lime
½ cup of sparkling water
optional: Sweetener such as monk fruit syrup of honey

1. Add 1 basil + 1 mint sprig in a cup and press them gently with a muddler or wooden spoon.
2. Add Sakara Detox Drops, lime juice, lime zest + optional sweetener. Mix well.
3. Add ice and top with sparkling water.
4. Garnish elixir with remaining basil, lime sprig + additional lime zest.

once a snowflake fell
on my brow and i loved
it so much and i kissed
it and it was happy and called its cousins

i reached to love them all

a spring rain and i stood perfectly
still and was a flower
